Owzzz. 
Yesterday I stretched my ear to a 12, straight from a 10 that had only been in for a week and it's all ripped inside + bloody and I have to put a plug in it by tomorrow so she wont ear me but I can't because it's swollen up like a bitch :[ 

Why's nothing ever easy?! Jeeesus mann. 

Anyway, yesterday was MINT :] 
Me and Adam went christmas shopping and I got absoluuuutely spoilt! He bought me a properrrr nice corset w/ knickers + suspenders + stockings, the whole worksssss, and allsorts! 

The corset is GORGEOUS. Anyone who knows me, knows that the way to my heart is deffo through lingere. I loveeee it :] 

And yeh. 
Fab day, all in all 

BESIDES THE FACT THAT MY EAR IS BEING A FUCKING BITCH. 

Anywah :] x

My profile's been updated =]
Go read kthnxbye

My Music Top 12.
+ Loaaaaaaaads more.

I TAG ALL OF YOU.
AHA. AHA. AHA.

Eeeeh. I've been watching Living TV TOO much. There get's to a point where you've watched "6ith sence with Colin Fry" and you start to believe yourself that you're a spirit medium. Jeez, I need a hobby. Or to do some coursework/revision, at the very least. Im confused. Hence why, here comes a rant. Lj- cutted so I dont inflict this on anyone who doesnt wish to see it. Tonight's rant - Boys. How confusing is all this? I hope this isnt just hormones, because if it is then I'm going to be SO angry at my bodies ability to let my hormones rule my head. The thing is, Im getting so confused. This is prbably cause of sitting around all day with nothing to do, too much time on my hands and too much to think about. There are a few matters that I need to get cleared, and someone once said that a problem shared is a problem halved, so here goes nothing: Boys. All my life I've never been majourly into boys. I've always felt like there were more important things to think about, but now Im not so sure. My number one rule was always never, ever let boys upset you and especially never work yourself up over one. But now.. Well. Lets say things arent running as smoothely as I always made them run, and Im descovering that everyday Im breaking my rules by getting wound up over something as stupid as boys. I'm getting angry at myself for what I sound like; A stupid, typical teenage girl. More to the point.. On one hand, There's Josh. We had a conversation a week or so ago, and he said he thought he'd made a mistake. He even put kisses at the end of the IM before he signed off. Then the next day it's like he's completely forgotten what he told me and Im getting confused. Again, on none uniform day, last week, we were acting as if we were together again. Then I try to get him to talk about it and he finds a way of avoiding it. Is he trying to give me a sign that he shouldnt have said it? I dont know! So Im here getting confused and wound up over it. I feel pathetic. Then there's everything that happened this time last year. Im more than over it now, and I can look back on it and laugh at my stupidity, but I cant stop thinking about it. What would I be like if I'd never had that relationship with Simon? Would I still be the same person, or would I be different? And finally, again, Im breaking my self-made rules by wanting a boyfriend. Why am I so intent on wanting a boy?! I cant quite put my finger on it. Is it the affection or just the plus side of having somebody to call "my boyfriend".

OW. My ear hurts.
Stupid alergy to earrings.

Anywho,
Kiddies, we are at risk.
Why I hear you ask?
Well. Because KATIE IS GOING TO FOB.
And if she does she WILL turn into a sertain little "hardXcore emo" gal that goes to my school.
And we will lose the bootuful, gothic Katie that we once knew and she will morph into a poetry writing, ghey eyeliner wearing, "none perfect", emoticon speaking, Josh loving WANNABEEEMOOOO.
[Yes, E-moo. It's a depressive cow.]

And she will write poetry in her Whinny The Pooh notebook because pooh bear is so hardXcore.

So y'see children, please, please.
We must do all we can to prevent her from going to that consert.

Thankyoubye.
